---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const withBase = (path) => `${baseUrl}${path.replace(/^\//, '')}`;
---
<BaseLayout title="Deploy · eunox" description="Deployment guides for every eunox tier: OSS Apache-2.0 in-process enforcement, and BSL self-host with Redis, Postgres, KMS, and Helm." activePage="deploy">

    <section class="hero hero-compact">
        <div class="hero-eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>Deploy</div>
        <h1>Deploy eunox <em>your way</em></h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">Two tiers, two deployment models. Pick the one that matches your infrastructure. Managed cloud tiers require no self-hosted infrastructure — sign up at <a href="https://eunox.dev">eunox.dev</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href={withBase('/')}>Home</a> &nbsp;›&nbsp; Deploy
    </nav>

    <main class="content-section">

        <h2>Choose your tier</h2>
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Tier</th>
                    <th>License</th>
                    <th>Infrastructure</th>
                    <th>Best for</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong><a href="#oss">OSS</a></strong></td>
                    <td>Apache-2.0</td>
                    <td>None — in-process</td>
                    <td>Individual developers, CI pipelines, local dev</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong><a href="#self-host">Self-Host</a></strong></td>
                    <td>BSL 1.1</td>
                    <td>BYO Redis, Postgres, KMS</td>
                    <td>Teams needing shared state, on-prem, air-gap</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Cloud Free / Team / Enterprise</strong></td>
                    <td>—</td>
                    <td>Managed by eunox</td>
                    <td>Fully managed — <a href="https://eunox.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">sign up at eunox.dev</a></td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <hr>

        <h2 id="oss">OSS — Apache-2.0 (no server required)</h2>

        <p>The <code>@eunox/mcp</code> package runs entirely in-process. All enforcement, call counting, and audit logging happens locally — no Redis, no Postgres, no gateway process.</p>

        <h3>Install</h3>
<pre><code>npm install -g @eunox/mcp</code></pre>

        <h3>Write a policy</h3>
<pre><code># policy.yaml
version: "1"

capabilities:
  - id: allow-read-only
    tools:
      - name: read_file
      - name: list_directory
    conditions:
      - type: path_prefix
        prefix: "/home/user/projects"
    audit:
      required: true

  - id: deny-writes
    tools:
      - name: write_file
      - name: delete_file
    effect: deny</code></pre>

        <p>The policy engine is default-deny: any tool not covered by an <code>allow</code> capability is blocked. See <a href="https://github.com/edgeobs/eunox/blob/main/docs/capability-manifest-guide.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">capability-manifest-guide.md</a> for all condition types.</p>

        <h3>Wire into Claude Desktop</h3>
<pre><code>// ~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json
{'{'}
  "mcpServers": {'{'}
    "filesystem-governed": {'{'}
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "@eunox/mcp",
        "--policy", "/path/to/policy.yaml",
        "--upstream", "npx",
        "--upstream-args",
        "@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem,/home/user/projects"
      ]
    {'}'}
  {'}'}
{'}'}</code></pre>

        <h3>Enable the local audit log</h3>
        <p>The proxy writes HMAC-chained audit records to <code>~/.eunox/audit.jsonl</code> automatically. Use <code>--audit-log</code> to override the path:</p>
<pre><code>eunox-mcp proxy --policy ./policy.yaml --audit-log ./audit.jsonl -- npx @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem /home/user/projects</code></pre>

        <p>Records are HMAC-chained for tamper-evidence. Inspect the log with <code>eunox-mcp validate-token</code> or summarise with <code>eunox-mcp stats</code>.</p>

        <h3>Upgrade when you need shared state</h3>
<pre><code>eunox-mcp upgrade-to-hosted \
  --gateway-url https://your-gateway.example.com \
  --api-key sk-&lt;prefix&gt;.&lt;secret&gt;</code></pre>

        <p>See the <a href="https://eunolabs.ai/blog/33-deploy-oss" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">full OSS deployment guide</a> and <a href="https://github.com/edgeobs/eunox/blob/main/docs/upgrade-to-hosted.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">upgrade-to-hosted.md</a> for the complete walkthrough.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2 id="self-host">Self-Host — BSL 1.1 (BYO infrastructure)</h2>

        <p>The self-host tier deploys the full gateway stack under your control: capability issuer, tool gateway, minter, posture emitter, and enterprise services. You manage Redis, Postgres, and a cloud KMS.</p>

        <div class="callout">
            <strong>License.</strong> BSL 1.1 — non-competing use; converts to Apache-2.0 four years after each release. <a href="https://github.com/edgeobs/eunox/blob/main/LICENSE" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Review the LICENSE</a> before deploying in a competing product.
        </div>

        <h3>What you need</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Docker ≥ 24 and Docker Compose ≥ 2 (or Kubernetes with Helm)</li>
            <li>A cloud KMS account: AWS KMS, Azure Key Vault, or GCP Cloud KMS</li>
            <li>Redis ≥ 6.2 (Sentinel or Cluster for production HA)</li>
            <li>Postgres ≥ 14</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Development setup (Docker Compose, no Redis/Postgres)</h3>
<pre><code># /srv/eunox/docker-compose.dev.yml
version: "3.9"
services:
  capability-issuer:
    image: ghcr.io/edgeobs/eunox/issuer:1.0.0
    env_file: /srv/eunox/issuer.env
    volumes: ["/srv/eunox/policies:/app/policies:ro"]
    ports: ["3001:3001"]

  tool-gateway:
    image: ghcr.io/edgeobs/eunox/gateway:1.0.0
    env_file: /srv/eunox/gateway.env
    volumes: ["/srv/eunox/keys:/app/keys:ro"]
    depends_on: [capability-issuer]
    ports: ["3002:3002", "127.0.0.1:3003:3003"]</code></pre>

<pre><code>docker compose -f /srv/eunox/docker-compose.dev.yml up -d</code></pre>

        <h3>Production deployment (Helm)</h3>
<pre><code>helm install eunox k8s/helm/eunox/ \
  --namespace eunox-system \
  --create-namespace \
  -f k8s/helm/eunox/values-prod.yaml</code></pre>

        <p>The Helm umbrella chart deploys all six services with individual HorizontalPodAutoscalers. For EKS and GKE cloud-specific guides, see <a href="https://github.com/edgeobs/eunox/blob/main/docs/deploy-eks.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">deploy-eks.md</a> and <a href="https://github.com/edgeobs/eunox/blob/main/docs/deploy-gke.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">deploy-gke.md</a>.</p>

        <h3>Redis HA requirement</h3>
        <p>In production mode (<code>NODE_ENV=production</code>), the gateway performs a fatal startup check: if any configured Redis URL points to a single-node instance, the service refuses to start. Configure Redis Sentinel or Redis Cluster for all Redis URLs.</p>

        <h3>Air-gap deployments</h3>
<pre><code># On a machine with internet access:
./scripts/pull-air-gap-images.sh
# Transfer air-gap-images.tar to the restricted network and load:
docker load &lt; air-gap-images.tar</code></pre>

        <p>The full image list is in <a href="https://github.com/edgeobs/eunox/blob/main/k8s/air-gap-images.txt" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><code>k8s/air-gap-images.txt</code></a>.</p>

        <h3>Wire @eunox/mcp to the gateway</h3>
<pre><code>{'{'}
  "mcpServers": {'{'}
    "my-server-governed": {'{'}
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "-y", "@eunox/mcp", "proxy",
        "--enforcer-url", "https://gateway.example.com",
        "--enforcer-api-key", "sk-&lt;prefix&gt;.&lt;secret&gt;",
        "--", "npx", "-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem", "/data"
      ]
    {'}'}
  {'}'}
{'}'}</code></pre>

        <h3>Full deployment guides</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="https://eunolabs.ai/blog/34-deploy-self-host" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Self-host deployment blog post</a> — step-by-step with KMS, Redis, Postgres, and Helm</li>
